article.description: — Taevion Kinsey had 22 points as Marshall defeated Wright State 96-88 on Friday night.
article.headline: Kinsey scores 22 to lift Marshall over Wright St. 96-88
article.linkText: Kinsey scores 22 to lift Marshall over Wright St. 96-88
article.story: HUNTINGTON, W.Va. -- — Taevion Kinsey had 22 points as Marshall defeated Wright State 96-88 on Friday night. Kinsey hit all 14 of his free-throw attempts. Andrew Taylor had 15 points and 11 assists for Marshall (1-0). Aymeric Toussaint added 13 points. Darius George had 11 points. Grant Basile scored a career-high 37 points for the Raiders (1-1). Tanner Holden added 25 points. Tim Finke had six points and 11 rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25------ Information from: Automated Insights, http://automatedinsights.com/ ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
